TestOutputWriteHasNoSpuriousChannel
/ Drift case 1 — the load-bearing reason this branch exists.
/
/ Step text `- write out %message%` (from Tests/Simple/Start.goal:5) carries no
/ channel clause. With per-action notes (os/system/modules/output/write.notes.md)
/ carrying the channel routing rule only when output.write is in the planner's
/ set, the LLM should emit:
/   parameters: { Data: %message% }   (no channel key)
/
/ Pre-fix shape this test forbids:
/   any 'channel' parameter on output.write when step text had no channel clause
/
/ Read .pr requires copying to a .txt first because '.pr' MIME deserializes to a
/ Goal object, defeating substring assertions. Copy → read as text → assert.
/ The companion C# test PLang.Tests/Builder/CompilePromptTests/DriftCaseArtifactTests.cs
/ does the structural check on the parsed Goal — both layers guard the same fact.
/
/ Architect's 3-fresh-cache verification rule runs externally:
/   rm -rf Tests/Simple/.build
/   PlangConsole/bin/Debug/net10.0/plang build /Tests/Simple   # then plang --test (x3)
- copy file '../../Simple/.build/start.pr' to 'start-out.txt', overwrite
- read file 'start-out.txt', write to %pr%
- assert %pr% contains '"text": "write out '
- assert %pr% does not contain '"name": "channel"'
